  "body": "Reference article: https://github.com/zsfelfoldi/go-ethereum/wiki/Light-Ethereum-Subprotocol-%28LES%29\r\n\r\nNewly added messages in the LES/2 protocol version (LPV2), `GetTxStatus/TxStatus`, used to request the full node to return the corresponding block hash and number\r\n\r\nAccording to my understanding, this is the beginning in the case of the buyer and seller:\r\nSeller <--- Transaction Hash --- Buyer\r\nSeller --- Transaction Hash --- > Full-Node\r\nSeller <--- Block Hash and Number --- Full-Node\r\n\r\nOther requests almost all need block hash as the basic request parameter:\r\n\r\nGetBlockHeaders\r\nGetBlockBodies\r\nGetReceipts\r\n...\r\n\r\nAnd after I read some of code, `GetTxStatus` does not even have ODR request type defined, **I just want to get a confirmation:**\r\n\r\nweb3 doesn't include function of `GetTxStatus`, and `GetTxStatus` and others are still under development?\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.8.12-unstable\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.10.3\r\nOperating System: darwin\r\n\r\n",
